column5: if thats 73 lbss, then i guess those kids are 5 feet tall too.
yeah, I don't think it's even 48"........but love old stories about big fish   it is a nice old photo
That would be lucky to weigh half that
Okay, I agree with everyone that the musky is nowhere close to 70+ lbs but.... here is a photo of some nice slabs from the golden years.  http://www.chippewaflowage.com/gallery/treelands/unknown3
As the average 6 year old is around 4' tall, the math speaks for itself! I would guess that it's at least 9" off the ground.

Not only that... it seemed the fish was held way in front of the camera while the 2 kids were more at the back.  Maybe it really was 7.2 lb? the decimal point got lost on the print/news after all these years....
check out the eyes on that thing, I think that may be a world record pickerel, not a slimy esox.  Either way, heck of a fish.  Not 73 lbs but I wouldn't mind tangling with it
I believe the musky was 72 lbs., and I am a good authority on fish weights   after all Laurie's bass was 28lbs.    Regards, Sam

Well its a nice old picture....BUT....it aint no 72lbs,.  .there is no way man,well i guess every year that past it just kept getting bigger & bigger.  ..LOL..LOL..LOL   thanks for showing us that pic   cheers
